Command `cat > check_solution.py << 'PY'
from solution import Solution

cases = [
    (13, 4, 2),
    (21, 21, 0),
    (14, 13, -1),
    # additional tests
    (1, 1, 0),
    (1, 0, 1),
    (0, 0, 0),
    (8, 1, -1),
    (10, 2, 1), # 1010 -> 0010, flip one 1
    (7, 0, 3), # 111 -> 000, flip three 1s
    (1024, 0, 1), # 10000000000 -> 0, flip one 1
    (1023, 512, 9), # 1023 has bits 0-9 set, 512 is bit9, need flip other 9 ones
]

s = Solution()
all_ok = True
for i, (n,k,exp) in enumerate(cases):
    out = s.minChanges(n,k)
    ok = out == exp
    print(i, n, k, out, exp, 'OK' if ok else 'FAIL')
    if not ok:
        all_ok = False

if all_ok:
    print('All tests passed')
else:
    print('Some tests failed')

cat > check_solution.py << 'PY'
from solution import Solution
cases = [
    (13, 4, 2),
    (21, 21, 0),
    (14, 13, -1),
    # additional tests
    (1, 1, 0),
    (1, 0, 1),
    (0, 0, 0),
    (8, 1, -1),
    (10, 2, 1), # 1010 -> 0010, flip one 1
    (7, 0, 3), # 111 -> 000, flip three 1s
    (1024, 0, 1), # 10000000000 -> 0, flip one 1
    (1023, 512, 9), # 1023 has bits 0-9 set, 512 is bit9, need flip other 9 ones
]
s = Solution()
all_ok = True
for i, (n,k,exp) in enumerate(cases):
    out = s.minChanges(n,k)
    ok = out == exp
    print(i, n, k, out, exp, 'OK' if ok else 'FAIL')
    if not ok:
        all_ok = False
if all_ok:
    print('All tests passed')
else:
    print('Some tests failed')
